Kinda crazy how difficult it really is to “do you boo”. I continuously find myself getting lost, forgetting who I really am because of all the pressures and expectations that surround us, especially living in LA. 

I am grateful for everything I have learned about myself through different relationships / human interactions I’ve had the last few years and I know that our self journey is something we will be working on every day for our entire life. 

I am FINALLY going to stop living for other people and begin to really focus on figuring out what I want and what truly makes me happy, and I hope anyone reading this does the same! 

If anyone has any tips/ advice for how to stay grounded and to stay focused on your own wants and needs come talk to me in the comments below ❤️❤️❤️ 

Love you guys !!

“The root of self-care is setting boundaries: it’s saying no to something in order to say yes to your own emotional, physical and mental well-being. ” - @nedratawwab 

I wanted to share this quote from this incredible book I’m reading that my therapist recommended called “Set boundaries, Find Peace” by @nedratawwab and I would one MILLION percent recommend everyone read it. 

It can be terrifying to say no. Right? Saying no often makes you feel like the bad guy; a terrible person, a terrible friend, partner, etc. However, that small moment of feeling like the asshole is almost completely overshadowed by the FLOOD of happiness you are going to feel when you have the ability to now focus on something that is going to push YOU further and feed YOUR soul. Also, if the person you are communicating your boundaries with doesn’t respect them, then you might want to reconsider them being a part of your life. Protect your energy friends. 🙌🏽🥰 ✨ Love you ❤️ Also, scroll to last slide to see this really cute mural I walked by yesterday with a friend that really spoke to us (:

Sooooo I started going to church recently and my mind has been opened up in literally a million ways. There’s so much I’d love to share from what I’ve been learning there but a quote that really stuck out to me yesterday that I wanted to share was “If you cannot experience pain, you cannot experience love” ❤️❤️

You can interpret this how you want but the fact is that life is going to be far from perfect even if you have chosen to give your life to Jesus or whoever/whatever you choose to believe in. It’s what we choose to do with those life experiences that can excel us to our next chapter in life. It’s all about the mindset. CHOOSE happiness, CHOOSE positivity, CHOOSE confidence, SET your boundaries and fill up YOUR cup before you keep pouring into other’s. YOU deserve the very best and don’t need NOBODY else’s approval! Life’s way to damn short to keep giving so much energy to everyone around us. Stay strong and remind yourself what a badass you are! 👊🏽👊🏽❤️‍🔥🤘🏽✨Love you!!

Decided to hit the reset button on my non-stop life in LA and came to Mexico for a whole month and I truly couldn’t be happier about this decision! Spent the first week in Cancún and now this is my first private villa in Tulúm for 10 days can you believe?! It truly feels like I’m living an absolute dream and I hope this inspires YOU to do something you’ve been thinking about but might be too scared to take that leap of faith to do it. This is your message to just DO IT cuz life can be way too damn short. I can’t wait to show y’all where im going next! (I think two more places after this) Keep staying tuned on my stories as well as my YouTube channel @nickmetos I’ve been documenting on there if you care to follow along on my journey of growth and self discovery 🤘🏽🫶🏽 Te amo ✨✨

All this time I’ve had no idea what “slugging” is and am sick of all the “trends” but then I realized it’s literally what I already do every night with my @egyptianmagic cream. It quite literally just means slathering on a large amount of moisturizer/ oil on your face before bed so your face gets some next level deep moisturization while you sleep 😴 💦 

The Egyptian magic cream is %100 natural and cruelty free and can be used for quite literally everything. I use it every night all over my face, neck, elbows, hands and feet. It is also my favorite makeup melting balm to use because it has no fragrances or dyes and doesn’t sting my eyes or make them foggy like other makeup melters 😌

This year has beennnnn…. Un montón 🤣 to say the least! ( “A LOT” in Spanish), Pero liiike, the biggest most MAJOR year of growth and learning of life lessons in the history of ever…… Lessons that I KNOW were supposed to happen so I can wake tf up and get back to my inner child and true self, 🫶🏽 and being around my family and people that truly have my best interest in mind is really helping get there. You can say I got a little “lost” in “Lost Angeles” , but honestly, I slayed it out there and I need to be proud of myself and grateful for the last 10 years of experiences and I’m really fcking excited to discover who I am by just literally being myself - why is that the hardest thing in the world to do tho? 🙈😭🤣 can I get an amen or is it just me? Hahahahaa. Gurl, we’re ALL out here trying to figure this thing out called life and I know this sounds GAY AF but I truly believe we are all in this together. Basically, long story long, doing my makeup and playing dress up for the cameras is something that truly makes me happy so you are going to be seeing me do a whole lot more of that on alllllll of my social channels (: 

Thanks for listening and thanks for being here and for following. If you’re not following yet, feel free to follow along and join the family and the journey! I can feel that it’s gonna be a fun one💋💋 I’m justtttt getting started baby!
